{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1392425161,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNzYzODU3Nw==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/48","origin":"github"},"title":"Packaging Format","message":"The current trend in related projects have been to abuse .ZIP and the likes (possibly with an XML manifest to close the idiocy circle).\nWhat is suggested here is to use a segmented model that splits into three segment subtypes (code, data, messages) ed25519 signatures for each segment (separate keys!). These can be updated individually, and updates append to previous segments, allowing the user to rollback to an earlier version.","files":null}]}